cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper discusses a framework for fault-tolerant SDN control plane, which involves network infrastructure, distributed systems, and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also addresses the issue of Byzantine failures, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the distributed operation of SDN controllers, which is related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The proposed framework also involves reconfiguring the control plane, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents a performance analysis of the proposed framework, which involves data analysis and modeling, falling under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
